features: THE SOFTEST, ALCOHOL & PARABEN-FREE WIPES FOR GENTLE CARE: Designed to clean and pamper your baby’s skin with every diaper change, our sensitive baby wipes feature a super-soft yet strong synthesis that makes cleaning a breeze. Completely free of parabens and alcohol, they will never cause irritation or dryness. The perfect choice even for newborns.

ENRICHED WITH SOOTHING ALOE VERA & VITAMIN E: Your baby’s bum and chubby thighs are always prone to diaper rash, chaffing and discomfort. To nourish your baby’s delicate skin, the MedPride scented baby wipes are infused with Aloe Vera and Vitamin E that offer proven soothing and moisturizing properties. Great for refreshing and protecting your little one’s silky skin!

CONVENIENT DISPENSER BOX FOR QUICK AND EASY USE: The user-friendly design of our easy dispense box allows you to grab a wipe just with one hand to ensure a comfortable and stress-free diaper changing routine. Plus, the secure closure will keep the disposable wipes fresh and moistened until use. No more dried-out baby cleaning wipes or flimsy sticker closures.

UNBEATABLE VALUE PACK – 24 PACKS X 80 WIPES EACH: For every parent, single-use baby wipes are a must-have. This great value pack will equip you with 24 packs that each contains 80 wipes. With 1920 baby wet wipes total, you will not run out anytime soon. Just keep a pack in your diaper bag, car, baby’s nursery or your diaper caddy and be ready to tackle any mess!

Reviewed in the United States on October 13, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Smells and clean great. I appreciate the additional seal so you know they won't dry out. The additional seal doesn't seem like it's meant to be removed, so I don't think that makes them easy to remove one handed as printed unless you crease and fold it back. The wipes aren't super thick or extraordinary, nothing to write home about.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Standard wipes, but I really like the closure system
reviews.reviewText: I would say these are pretty standard wipes. The size is a bit smaller than the premium wipes. They are also a bit thinner. However, I would say they are comparable to big box store brands.What I like most about these wipes is the packaging. My babies are no longer in diapers so we don't go through wipes like we once did, but I'm never without wipes in my car and in my bag. The package is more compact than other wipes, which I appreciate, and the closure system has both the resealable adhesive AND the plastic "door." This helps to keep the moisture in so they don't dry out as quickly. I LOVE this feature!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Pros and cons.....
reviews.reviewText: Pros: I like the amount of moisture in the wipe and they are soft.Cons: as others have stated they are on the small side and I do not like to use scented products on my granddaughter. The fewer chemicals on her skin the better. This product contains more additives than what we normally use.Note: the listing says that Shield Line, LLC of NJ is the manufacturer but on the back of the individual package it says they are made in China for the seller. The listing should be corrected

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars A very strong awful scent. Couldn’t even open a pack.
reviews.reviewText: I knew that these baby wipes were scented when I ordered a box of them. I just thought, How bad can the scent be? They’re made for babies.When I received the box (It was quite heavy. Never thought baby wipes were so heavy, but there were a lot of them.), I brought it inside the house and noticed a mild scent which was similar to a detergent scent. However, when I opened the box, the scent changed and became very strong. I cannot even describe the scent except it smelled like a very heavy awful perfume. I could not stand the smell to the extent that I could not even bring myself to open a pack of wipes. I could not even keep them inside the house. I took the box out into the garage. The next day I went into the garage, and it smelled so bad I had to take the box outside.So I am not sure what was wrong with the box of wipes I got or if they are just in general so heavily scented. I am not sure why they have to be scented like that to be used on babies. I admit I am a bit sensitive to scents, but my husband could not stand the smell either.My review does not include any comments on the wipes themselves as I never even opened a pack.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars They are decent wipes
reviews.reviewText: These wipes are decent when compared to other wipes I use. They are plenty moist. I'm not a fan of scented wipes only because they can cause reactions to the skin. The scent itself is fine. The wipes are a little smaller than I prefer. I like them a little larger to help clean up big messes.
